1
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:32,020
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,950
[Episode 27]

3
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:18,310
Not sure if they are friends or foes.

4
00:02:34,820 --> 00:02:35,780
Squad...

5
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:36,930
What do you want?

6
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:37,790
I...

7
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:43,960
My loving sweetheart with a round face.

8
00:02:48,990 --> 00:02:53,130
A mouth so slick.

9
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:15,400
That cherry-like little mouth.

10
00:03:15,790 --> 00:03:20,280
I love you to death, my sister-in-law.

11
00:03:41,150 --> 00:03:46,800
Wield our broadswords
at the Japanese invaders' heads!

12
00:03:47,140 --> 00:03:50,510
Patriotic countrymen across the nation,

13
00:03:50,930 --> 00:03:54,370
the day for resistance has come.

14
00:03:54,660 --> 00:04:00,270
-The day for resistance has come!
-The day for resistance has come!

15
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:05,800
They're Chinese.

16
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:09,900
Stay cautious.

17
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:44,860
Which unit are you from?

18
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,210
We are...

19
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:52,420
from the New Fourth Army
Field Service Group.

20
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,860
The Communist army, huh?

21
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,050
[New Fourth Army Field Service Group,
Fu Fan]

22
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,470
Hey, isn't it a waste of power?

23
00:05:18,470 --> 00:05:19,850
But they are trying to intimidate us.

24
00:05:19,850 --> 00:05:21,930
Enough. Stop messing with them.

25
00:05:22,330 --> 00:05:23,250
Put it down.

26
00:05:25,850 --> 00:05:27,070
You too, put it away.

27
00:05:28,970 --> 00:05:30,020
You, Zhou,

28
00:05:30,180 --> 00:05:31,640
put down the flashlights.

29
00:05:32,780 --> 00:05:33,980
Which unit are you from?

30
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:35,450
We are wounded soldiers and medical staff

31
00:05:35,450 --> 00:05:38,090
who broke out
from the Wuhan Field Hospital.

32
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:40,000
Since we're all fighting the Japanese,

33
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,730
why not put down our guns first?

34
00:05:42,010 --> 00:05:44,409
Great. I was thinking the same thing.

35
00:05:57,890 --> 00:05:58,420
Ye Sheng.

36
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,000
Yes!

37
00:05:59,240 --> 00:05:59,990
Release them.

38
00:05:59,990 --> 00:06:00,550
Yes.

39
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:06,000
My gun. Give it back to me!

40
00:06:10,010 --> 00:06:11,160
This big old lubber

41
00:06:11,790 --> 00:06:13,850
can actually sing "The Sword March."

42
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:15,960
Anything wrong with singing that?

43
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,410
What time is it now?

44
00:06:17,590 --> 00:06:20,430
Is there a problem with singing
about fighting Japanese invaders?

45
00:06:20,430 --> 00:06:22,750
At least it is better than
what you reactionary warlords sing,

46
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:25,560
"My loving sweetheart with a round face

47
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,140
and a cherry-like mouth."

48
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:28,680
How disgusting!

49
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,040
Halt!

50
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,080
Who were you spitting at?

51
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:33,950
What's wrong with me singing about girls?

52
00:06:33,950 --> 00:06:35,920
Whatever we sing,
we are still a legitimate troop,

53
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:38,210
who are way better
than you ragtag soldiers!

54
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:39,430
Who are you calling "ragtag soldiers"?

55
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:40,159
You, exactly!

56
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:41,500
You'd better watch your mouth!

57
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,230
I am picking on you now. So what?

58
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,520
It was pitch dark,
so I fell for your trap.

59
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,330
Hold it for me.

60
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,600
How about a fair fight with me now?

61
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,420
Bring it on.

62
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:51,120
I...

63
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:52,740
Squad Leader of Squad Three!

64
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:53,770
Keep it down,

65
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,920
or the Japanese will be drawn here.

66
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,880
Full of energy with nowhere to spend it,
are you, Ye Sheng?

67
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:59,330
If you deem yourself good,

68
00:06:59,330 --> 00:07:02,590
then get on the battlefield
to kill the Japanese invaders.

69
00:07:04,970 --> 00:07:05,730
Come here!

70
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:09,870
Zhou.

71
00:07:09,890 --> 00:07:10,370
Yes!

72
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,000
Go out and stand guard.

73
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,480
Got it!

74
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,480
Everyone, rest on the spot.

75
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,040
Yes!

76
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:19,630
Liu.

77
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,000
Yes.

78
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:20,720
Stand guard.

79
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,240
Got it.

80
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:24,110
Mr. Zhang, you should take a rest too.

81
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:27,590
Come on, let me check your hand.

82
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:32,230
Sit down.

83
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:40,280
No need to go inside.

84
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:41,480
It's fine here.

85
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:58,490
Spare a sip of your water for me.

86
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:00,940
There isn't a drop left.

87
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:02,630
Yuanzheng, what about yours?

88
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:03,560
Long gone.

89
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:05,550
Does anyone have water?

90
00:08:05,550 --> 00:08:06,690
No one, I guess.

91
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:22,410
Commissar, have some water.

92
00:08:22,810 --> 00:08:24,600
Let the comrades have it first.

93
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:27,520
I wish that tap were on our side.

94
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:28,800
Hurry and search.

95
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,450
See if there is a tap around.

96
00:08:31,650 --> 00:08:33,789
Go look for it. Now!

97
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:43,559
Come over! Come!

98
00:08:43,580 --> 00:08:46,060
Remove this stuff. Get your canteens over.

99
00:08:46,990 --> 00:08:47,790
There is a tap.

100
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:52,270
Come on.

101
00:08:58,860 --> 00:08:59,550
Move aside!

102
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:00,780
Why is there no water?

103
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:10,780
Suck some from the tap!

104
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,720
Fu Fan, this can wait.

105
00:09:12,770 --> 00:09:14,030
Have some water first.

106
00:09:18,050 --> 00:09:19,450
I got a mouth full of rust.

107
00:09:20,730 --> 00:09:22,520
Even the tap is bullying us.

108
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,050
Ye Sheng.

109
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,640
Yes.

110
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,580
Send some water to those people.

111
00:09:35,730 --> 00:09:36,690
Tell them to come over

112
00:09:36,690 --> 00:09:38,690
if they need to fill their canteens.

113
00:09:39,590 --> 00:09:40,190
Yes.

114
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:49,590
Our commissar told me to give you this.

115
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,160
Thank you.

116
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,530
How did your commander's hand get injured?

117
00:10:01,530 --> 00:10:03,600
His purlicue was pierced by shrapnel.

118
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,010
The wound has festered now.

119
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:07,110
Our commissar has another message for you—

120
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:09,350
come fill your canteens if needed.

121
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:14,520
-W-We can get water there?
-Yes, go.

122
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:15,780
-Hurry!
-Take out your canteens!

123
00:10:15,780 --> 00:10:17,290
Give me your canteens. Quick!

124
00:10:17,290 --> 00:10:19,090
Bring it to the wounded outside.

125
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:20,520
Got it.

126
00:10:20,570 --> 00:10:22,210
I'm on it.

127
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:23,500
Yuanzheng.

128
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:24,070
Yes.

129
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,910
Go get Dr. Luo over.

130
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:27,960
Tell him
this commander's hand is injured.

131
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,920
Ask him to take a look.

132
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:29,430
Yes!

133
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:35,870
Who else has water?

134
00:10:35,890 --> 00:10:37,010
It's all used up.

135
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,930
Director! Where is Dr. Luo?

136
00:10:46,930 --> 00:10:47,670
Any water here?

137
00:10:47,670 --> 00:10:49,210
A wounded man needs medical help inside.

138
00:10:49,210 --> 00:10:50,610
-Xiaoyue!
-Come with me!

139
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:52,330
Let's go.

140
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:55,980
Turn it on a bit more.

141
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:57,900
The water was flowing just now, wasn't it?

142
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,330
The tap outside bullies us.

143
00:10:59,330 --> 00:11:00,520
And the one inside does the same.

144
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,750
Stop with this useless whining.

145
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,000
Suck from the tap now.

146
00:11:16,890 --> 00:11:18,020
H-Here comes water!

147
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:19,680
D-Don't waste it!

148
00:11:19,710 --> 00:11:20,770
Let me take a few sips first.

149
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:21,630
Let me through!

150
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:23,560
Here they are.

151
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:24,550
Zuliang.

152
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:26,780
The one sitting there is their commander.

153
00:11:26,780 --> 00:11:28,980
His hand is injured. Check on his wound.

154
00:11:32,540 --> 00:11:34,080
Can we take a look?

155
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,340
And you are?

156
00:11:35,390 --> 00:11:36,360
We are medics.

157
00:11:36,610 --> 00:11:38,090
Great. Go ahead, please.

158
00:11:39,970 --> 00:11:41,190
Bring Zhou with you to see

159
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:42,510
if the Japanese have new movements.

160
00:11:42,510 --> 00:11:43,150
Got it.

161
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:46,390
Doctor,

162
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:48,550
we're out of medicine and gauze.

163
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:50,230
I just disinfected the wound.

164
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,800
Luckily, the bones are fine.

165
00:11:52,970 --> 00:11:54,970
But the wound is severely inflamed.

166
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:57,240
I need to clear the dead tissue first.

167
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:59,200
Bear with it. It'll hurt a little.

168
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,720
No problem. Just do it.

169
00:12:00,980 --> 00:12:02,020
Thank you so much.

170
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:13,020
Alright, give me the gauze.

171
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:18,390
Try not to use this hand for anything.

172
00:12:18,390 --> 00:12:19,740
It'll heal in a few days.

173
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,160
Thank you.

174
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:22,750
You're Mr. Xie?

175
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:25,630
I heard your speech in Wuhan.

176
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:27,410
I stared at you for a long time

177
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,270
and found you so familiar.

178
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:30,680
I was just wondering

179
00:12:30,710 --> 00:12:33,240
-if you were Professor Shen's...
-Yes, right.

180
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,240
I am Professor Shen's student,
named Luo Zuliang.

181
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:37,360
That's right. You're Luo Zuliang.

182
00:12:37,670 --> 00:12:38,640
What brings you here?

183
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:41,040
I retreated with the other hospital staff.

184
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:43,260
What a coincidence.

185
00:12:43,510 --> 00:12:45,170
This really is a coincidence.

186
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,170
Alright, I can handle it myself.

187
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:47,770
It's done.

188
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:48,470
Thank you.

189
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:49,360
Thank you.

190
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,480
Yunkui, I met an acquaintance.

191
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,290
This is Mr. Xie who gave a speech in Wuhan

192
00:12:54,290 --> 00:12:56,040
and enlightened me.

193
00:12:58,280 --> 00:12:59,170
This is...

194
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,010
My cousin, named Zhang Yunkui.

195
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,810
Nice to meet you, Mr. Zhang.

196
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:05,430
I'm the New Fourth Army
Field Service Group's political commissar.

197
00:13:05,430 --> 00:13:06,630
My name is Xie Yufeng.

198
00:13:08,450 --> 00:13:10,640
Nice to meet you. I'm Zhang Yunkui.

199
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,930
Here, please meet a comrade

200
00:13:13,330 --> 00:13:14,860
of our field service group,

201
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:15,460
Fu Fan.

202
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:16,150
Hello.

203
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:16,770
Hello.

204
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:18,010
And this

205
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,480
miraculously strong man

206
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,360
who fixed the water pipes
with several punches

207
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,090
is Company Commander Ye Sheng.

208
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,140
Hello.

209
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,980
Hello, Company Commander Ye.

210
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:30,730
Where did you come from?

211
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:32,180
We came
from the Eighth Route Army Office.

212
00:13:32,180 --> 00:13:34,270
We are also with many comrades
from the Field Service Group

213
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:36,310
and training cadres
from classes for guerrilla warfare.

214
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:37,210
What about you lot?

215
00:13:37,210 --> 00:13:38,160
Didn't I just tell you?

216
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,140
I am with some wounded soldiers
from the Wuhan Field Hospital,

217
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:42,160
who used to serve in different units.

218
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,490
Obviously so, I'd say.

219
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:45,770
We don't have much medicine left.

220
00:13:45,770 --> 00:13:47,300
This is all we can offer you.

221
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:49,750
It's already enough to save several lives.

222
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:50,440
Thank you.

223
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:52,650
Zuliang, go talk to the Director.

224
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:54,200
Find out if we can give them
more medicine.

225
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:54,680
Got it.

226
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:56,340
Lyu, talk to the Director.

227
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:56,960
Sure.

228
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,280
I have some potatoes here.

229
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:00,860
If you don't mind,

230
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:01,910
they're yours to eat.

231
00:14:01,910 --> 00:14:02,790
This is great.

232
00:14:02,990 --> 00:14:05,640
We only brought medicine with us
during the urgent evacuation.

233
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:06,370
Thank you.

234
00:14:06,810 --> 00:14:08,210
We're glad you like them.

235
00:14:08,390 --> 00:14:09,250
Zuliang, look,

236
00:14:09,340 --> 00:14:11,400
many of their men are injured as well.

237
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:13,910
Check on them and provide medical help.

238
00:14:13,910 --> 00:14:14,970
Let me lead the way.

239
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:20,110
Thanks.

240
00:14:23,380 --> 00:14:25,760
Squad Leader Ma, here comes a doctor.

241
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:26,490
How is he?

242
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:28,250
Help me lift up the leg, please.

243
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:29,400
Commissar Xie,

244
00:14:30,060 --> 00:14:31,640
what do you plan to do next?

245
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:34,020
The organization
has arranged a boat for us.

246
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:35,610
We'll board it tomorrow morning.

247
00:14:35,610 --> 00:14:36,870
What's your plan then?

248
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,390
About the same as yours.

249
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:40,010
We'll try if we can bring these many

250
00:14:40,010 --> 00:14:41,550
wounded soldiers to the riverbank.

251
00:14:41,550 --> 00:14:42,350
If that works,

252
00:14:42,380 --> 00:14:44,510
we'll make other arrangements there.

253
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,630
A commonly seen injury.

254
00:14:52,630 --> 00:14:54,750
Cleanse, disinfect, and bandage it.

255
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,250
Xiaoyue, you handle this.

256
00:14:56,250 --> 00:14:57,030
I'll head over there.

257
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:57,510
Got it.

258
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:00,570
It'll take just a moment.

259
00:15:00,570 --> 00:15:01,830
Hey, let me take a look.

260
00:15:02,780 --> 00:15:04,600
He has a shrapnel cut. I've treated it,

261
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,200
but the pain is still unbearable.

262
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,060
Where exactly?

263
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:07,700
Here.

264
00:15:07,730 --> 00:15:08,420
Let me see.

265
00:15:09,210 --> 00:15:10,010
Hang in there.

266
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:11,680
Sure. Get it started.

267
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:16,130
-Bear with it. Hang in there.
-Squad Leader Ma.

268
00:15:16,130 --> 00:15:18,030
You are really something, young lady.

269
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:20,410
Any other girl would have been scared away
by now.

270
00:15:20,410 --> 00:15:23,140
The longer I've been a nurse,
the less fear I have.

271
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:24,570
What can I do to help?

272
00:15:25,410 --> 00:15:27,140
Apply medicine on the patient.

273
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:28,400
Here.

274
00:15:29,170 --> 00:15:29,680
Got it.

275
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:31,970
How long have you been a nurse?

276
00:15:31,970 --> 00:15:32,900
Several months.

277
00:15:33,130 --> 00:15:36,370
But with hundreds of wounded soldiers
coming and going every day,

278
00:15:36,370 --> 00:15:37,270
the Director says

279
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,690
I can gain a year's experience
within just one month.

280
00:15:39,690 --> 00:15:42,150
It's a pleasure to meet you.
My name is Fu Fan.

281
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:43,440
I'm Han Xiaoyue.

282
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:46,740
Get a good rest.

283
00:15:46,870 --> 00:15:47,510
Thank you.

284
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:48,760
Your moves are quick.

285
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:02,570
I've benefited so much
from our all-night talk.

286
00:16:03,870 --> 00:16:06,870
One conversation with you
is worth ten years of study.

287
00:16:07,370 --> 00:16:08,090
Come on.

288
00:16:08,170 --> 00:16:08,800
Let's toast with water. Cheers.

289
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,370
Cheers.

290
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,100
Report!

291
00:16:14,350 --> 00:16:15,290
We detected a group of Japanese—

292
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:17,640
quite a few, indeed. They're heading here.

293
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:19,120
Did you catch a good look?

294
00:16:19,230 --> 00:16:20,130
How many of them?

295
00:16:20,130 --> 00:16:22,100
About a company, with two tanks.

296
00:16:22,130 --> 00:16:22,910
How far are they?

297
00:16:22,910 --> 00:16:23,900
Two kilometers or so.

298
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:25,160
Zhou is keeping guard.

299
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:26,040
We're not the target

300
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,220
of the Japanese vanguard.

301
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:28,940
The real danger lies in
their follow-up troops,

302
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:31,030
as the Japanese will send infantry
to scout.

303
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,180
Everyone, find cover and stay alert!

304
00:16:32,180 --> 00:16:32,780
Yes!

305
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:34,570
Look, you go over there.

306
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,030
Liu, inform the entire unit.

307
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:37,630
After the Japanese vanguard passes,

308
00:16:37,630 --> 00:16:38,510
all of us must evacuate.

309
00:16:38,510 --> 00:16:38,840
Yes!

310
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:41,030
Ye Sheng, get everything lined up
for a battle.

311
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:41,670
Yes!

312
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:48,880
Commissar Xie.

313
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,330
Last night, you said there would be a boat

314
00:16:54,330 --> 00:16:55,300
by the riverbank. Right?

315
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:55,960
Yes, right.

316
00:16:57,380 --> 00:16:59,030
I have a favor to ask,
but it may seem too much.

317
00:16:59,030 --> 00:16:59,640
Just say it.

318
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:01,580
Could you bring
our wounded soldiers and medics

319
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:03,580
with you and let them board the boat?

320
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:07,040
Excuse me for a minute, will you?

321
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:10,569
Party subgroup members,
huddle up for a meeting.

322
00:17:10,569 --> 00:17:11,200
Liu.

323
00:17:12,859 --> 00:17:14,109
A situation has come up.

324
00:17:14,109 --> 00:17:15,050
They asked if we could

325
00:17:15,050 --> 00:17:16,920
bring all their wounded soldiers with us.

326
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:17,960
What do you think?

327
00:17:18,349 --> 00:17:19,310
I checked just now.

328
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:20,880
They have over 30 wounded soldiers

329
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,790
in total,
among which 15 are severely injured.

330
00:17:22,790 --> 00:17:24,480
They'll be a burden
if we take them with us.

331
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,220
What good will that do us?

332
00:17:25,220 --> 00:17:26,940
No, that's not the right way
of thinking about it.

333
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:28,369
The tactics of you Sichuan Army
won't work here.

334
00:17:28,369 --> 00:17:29,470
We have too few fighters now.

335
00:17:29,470 --> 00:17:30,310
We should gather all forces

336
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:31,810
and use the tactics of us Central Army.

337
00:17:31,810 --> 00:17:33,260
Ye Sheng, I'm afraid

338
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:34,590
I can't agree with you.

339
00:17:34,710 --> 00:17:36,190
Six of our men are severely wounded
as well.

340
00:17:36,190 --> 00:17:37,850
Do you think they can run fast?

341
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,600
Or do they have wings

342
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:40,940
that can help them fly?

343
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,270
Fu Fan, what's your opinion?

344
00:17:44,270 --> 00:17:45,850
We shouldn't draw boundaries
at a time like this.

345
00:17:45,850 --> 00:17:47,510
Saving lives is the priority.

346
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:48,310
Liu.

347
00:17:48,330 --> 00:17:50,650
I agree.
But one boat can't fit all the people.

348
00:17:50,650 --> 00:17:52,710
Let's be quick and make a second trip.

349
00:17:53,850 --> 00:17:55,260
I will firmly obey orders.

350
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:56,370
It's settled then.

351
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,790
-Yes.
-That way, we can either attack or defend.

352
00:17:59,810 --> 00:18:01,100
Sorry to interrupt.

353
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:01,850
Mr. Zhang,

354
00:18:02,210 --> 00:18:04,870
leave the wounded to us.
We'll take care of them.

355
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:08,070
Zuliang, get the wounded ready.

356
00:18:08,090 --> 00:18:09,860
You will all go with Commissar Xie later.

357
00:18:09,860 --> 00:18:11,380
Yes. But what about you?

358
00:18:12,380 --> 00:18:13,320
Why divide into two groups

359
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:14,750
since we can all leave this place?

360
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:15,490
Let's go together.

361
00:18:15,490 --> 00:18:16,850
No. The wounded walk too slowly.

362
00:18:16,850 --> 00:18:18,450
The Japanese infantry will soon notice us.

363
00:18:18,450 --> 00:18:19,240
In my opinion,

364
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,670
we should all run as fast as we can.

365
00:18:20,670 --> 00:18:22,490
Those who can't move
shouldn't drag others down, right?

366
00:18:22,490 --> 00:18:23,210
That means to leave

367
00:18:23,210 --> 00:18:25,080
the wounded here to die, doesn't it?

368
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:25,950
I'll stay to stall the Japanese

369
00:18:25,950 --> 00:18:27,250
so you can have time for the escape.

370
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:28,890
Won't you be killing yourself

371
00:18:28,890 --> 00:18:29,910
by sending us away and staying behind?

372
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:30,980
That's right, Zhang.

373
00:18:30,980 --> 00:18:32,770
We're not even an established unit now.

374
00:18:32,770 --> 00:18:33,750
It's not too late to run.

375
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:35,680
No one can blame you. Let's just go.

376
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:36,680
Right.

377
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:38,850
I don't belong to a unit
or have an insignia now.

378
00:18:38,850 --> 00:18:40,110
But a man should die a worthy death.

379
00:18:40,110 --> 00:18:41,960
If I die, the country lives.

380
00:18:42,210 --> 00:18:43,650
Given that, I choose to die now.

381
00:18:43,650 --> 00:18:44,930
Leave me as much ammunition as you can.

382
00:18:44,930 --> 00:18:46,660
-For you, I will...
-I'll stay.

383
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:47,550
Why?

384
00:18:47,850 --> 00:18:50,580
At least I can bandage your wounds
if you get hurt.

385
00:18:51,020 --> 00:18:52,700
How will you cope when we're all gone?

386
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:53,550
But do you even know

387
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:55,750
how to load a gun if I give you one?

388
00:18:56,230 --> 00:18:57,580
What I'm issuing now is an order.

389
00:18:57,580 --> 00:18:59,180
And you must obey it. Leave.

390
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:02,320
Leave right now!

391
00:19:02,610 --> 00:19:04,290
Xiaoyue, let's go!

392
00:19:05,110 --> 00:19:05,590
Go!

393
00:19:05,610 --> 00:19:07,170
Yes, Miss Xiaoyue, hurry and leave.

394
00:19:07,170 --> 00:19:08,830
Mr. Zhang, I'll stay with you.

395
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,520
I promised to stick with you.

396
00:19:10,590 --> 00:19:12,660
I will always stick with you,
even if death awaits me.

397
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:14,140
I've been a soldier for over 20 years.

398
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:17,060
What I'm most proud of
is that I'm a good judge of character.

399
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:18,060
But this time, why would I

400
00:19:18,060 --> 00:19:20,190
decide to follow a blockhead like you?

401
00:19:21,330 --> 00:19:22,960
Thank you, You,

402
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:25,270
for being with me
from Tai'erzhuang to Wuhan.

403
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:27,600
We said we'd make a name for ourselves.

404
00:19:28,190 --> 00:19:28,890
But I'm sorry.

405
00:19:28,890 --> 00:19:30,310
I have to break my word again.

406
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:31,620
I can't ask you to stay with me.

407
00:19:31,620 --> 00:19:32,880
You're free to go. I won't blame you.

408
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,080
The choice is yours.

409
00:19:34,860 --> 00:19:36,010
Come on, let's go.

410
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,370
Squad Leader of Squad Three!
Who was it that put his arm

411
00:19:38,370 --> 00:19:40,200
around my shoulder
and said we were brothers?

412
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,510
What will that make of you if you run now?

413
00:19:41,510 --> 00:19:42,270
A deserter!

414
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:43,990
Ask yourself and answer from your heart—

415
00:19:43,990 --> 00:19:45,170
don't you feel guilty at all?

416
00:19:45,170 --> 00:19:46,890
I have a clear conscience!

417
00:19:47,070 --> 00:19:49,360
We fought from Sichuan to Tai'erzhuang,

418
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:50,830
and now to Wuhan.

419
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,130
How many people on the way

420
00:19:52,130 --> 00:19:53,990
have treated us as decent humans?

421
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:56,070
By bringing these
wounded and sick soldiers here

422
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:57,370
from the Wuhan Military Field Hospital,

423
00:19:57,370 --> 00:19:58,780
we have done everything we could!

424
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:02,210
It's time they started
fending for themselves.

425
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:03,680
Heaven might be looking at this,

426
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:04,890
but it won't blame me.

427
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:06,440
I'll even receive praise for this!

428
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:06,950
Brother, let's go!

429
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:07,650
Run, I dare you!

430
00:20:07,650 --> 00:20:08,380
Out of my way!

431
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,040
Don't you walk another step!

432
00:20:12,060 --> 00:20:14,430
Brother, what's with you now?

433
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:18,440
All he said was some gibberish.

434
00:20:18,460 --> 00:20:20,350
What? Did that change your mind?

435
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:22,740
You are a cat with 9 lives
that bends with the wind.

436
00:20:22,740 --> 00:20:23,900
You go whichever way the wind blows.

437
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,490
Forget about it, will you?

438
00:20:25,510 --> 00:20:26,700
I once promised to go

439
00:20:26,730 --> 00:20:28,390
wherever he goes.

440
00:20:28,420 --> 00:20:29,150
As a man of integrity,

441
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:30,590
I can't go back on my word, can I?

442
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:32,870
Just think of me
as a supporter of a blockhead now.

443
00:20:32,870 --> 00:20:34,240
Besides, I have 9 lives, don't I?

444
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,260
I won't necessarily die if I stay, right?

445
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:38,460
You have your own legs.

446
00:20:38,490 --> 00:20:39,830
Feel free to go wherever you want.

447
00:20:39,830 --> 00:20:42,660
I will by no means blame you.

448
00:20:49,180 --> 00:20:50,120
Fine then.

449
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:52,240
Consider what I said to be nonsense.

450
00:20:55,030 --> 00:20:55,810
The Japanese have arrived.

451
00:20:55,810 --> 00:20:57,980
Zhou, go tell all non-combatants
to evacuate

452
00:20:57,980 --> 00:20:58,930
as per my order.

453
00:20:58,960 --> 00:20:59,440
Yes!

454
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:00,680
Everyone, get ready.

455
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,880
Attack the Japanese
only when they draw near.

456
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:03,720
-Yes!
-Yes!

457
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:46,750
Zhang, it's me!

458
00:21:53,150 --> 00:21:54,390
I especially got you these.

459
00:21:54,390 --> 00:21:55,620
Two magazines of bullets for your pistol.

460
00:21:55,620 --> 00:21:57,550
Sixty Hanyang 88 pointed bullets.

461
00:21:57,610 --> 00:21:58,940
Eight grenades as well.

462
00:21:59,030 --> 00:22:00,740
I'm offering you my last stash.

463
00:22:00,740 --> 00:22:01,730
Hope you won't scoff at it.

464
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:02,860
How generous of you.

465
00:22:03,310 --> 00:22:04,000
You!

466
00:22:04,030 --> 00:22:04,640
Yes.

467
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:06,200
Distribute these to our men.

468
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:06,720
Yes!

469
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,560
I got it.

470
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:13,290
So you came back for death.

471
00:22:16,180 --> 00:22:17,440
What's that nonsense?

472
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:19,330
Who says coming back means death?

473
00:22:19,330 --> 00:22:20,990
Can't we find a way to survive?

474
00:22:21,410 --> 00:22:24,720
Only living souls can fight
a protracted war, right?

475
00:22:25,110 --> 00:22:29,290
Plus, aren't we always encouraged
to unite to resist the Japanese invasion?

476
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:30,760
Let's not just talk the talk.

477
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:32,360
It's time we walked the walk.

478
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:33,200
I've long heard

479
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:35,050
that you people excel in
promoting your political ideology.

480
00:22:35,050 --> 00:22:37,540
That truly sank in me today.

481
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:40,240
I just happened to get a chance.

482
00:22:40,470 --> 00:22:42,720
I heard you strategize
brilliantly earlier.

483
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:44,440
You must be an excellent fighter.

484
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:46,040
Tell me your plan for the battle.

485
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,310
First of all, protect ourselves.

486
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:48,980
Stall the enemy for as long as possible.

487
00:22:48,980 --> 00:22:50,970
Firmly oppose the retreat-only mentality
with no advance.

488
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:51,440
The advance-only

489
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:54,500
rash adventurism with no retreat
is also to be avoided.

490
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,750
I'm correct, aren't I?

491
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:57,220
You're not half bad.

492
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,930
So you've read
Chairman Mao's "On Protracted War"?

493
00:22:59,930 --> 00:23:01,910
Just some parts, not its entirety.

494
00:23:02,220 --> 00:23:03,420
To be honest, though,

495
00:23:03,860 --> 00:23:05,860
he really is an amazing strategist.

496
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,680
Close to perfection.

497
00:23:08,250 --> 00:23:11,050
I'll tell you more about it
when there's a chance.

498
00:23:12,930 --> 00:23:14,980
Can't that boat of yours
make one more trip?

499
00:23:14,980 --> 00:23:15,750
Yes, it can.

500
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:18,010
But too bad that you'll be dead by then.

501
00:23:18,010 --> 00:23:19,470
No, that'll be how you end.

502
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:51,660
Here comes the enemy!

503
00:24:06,620 --> 00:24:07,530
Stay alert!

504
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:09,610
There might be an ambush!

505
00:24:09,970 --> 00:24:10,980
Conduct a check!

506
00:24:20,940 --> 00:24:21,540
Fire!

507
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:00,570
Enemy attack!

508
00:25:00,570 --> 00:25:01,130
Ye Sheng!

509
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:01,750
Got it!

510
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:05,200
Quick!

511
00:25:07,860 --> 00:25:09,500
Come, this way!

512
00:25:31,570 --> 00:25:32,220
Hurry!

513
00:25:36,860 --> 00:25:37,440
Ye Sheng!

514
00:25:37,470 --> 00:25:37,950
Yes!

515
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:43,820
This way!

516
00:26:15,820 --> 00:26:16,460
Run!

517
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,660
Give me your backpack!

518
00:26:56,470 --> 00:26:57,340
Your bag!

519
00:27:18,060 --> 00:27:18,780
Retreat!

520
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:24,480
Hurry! Run!

521
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:28,200
Zhou!

522
00:27:28,220 --> 00:27:29,140
Don't go there!

523
00:27:29,810 --> 00:27:30,610
Zhou Wenpeng!

524
00:27:35,750 --> 00:27:36,480
Run!

525
00:27:40,310 --> 00:27:42,240
-Zhou Wenpeng!
-Move!

526
00:27:58,540 --> 00:28:00,450
Go, quick!

527
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:01,720
Nice and slow.

528
00:28:01,830 --> 00:28:03,240
Do be careful.

529
00:28:06,030 --> 00:28:07,110
Come on, keep up!

530
00:28:07,530 --> 00:28:08,480
Xiaoyue, what are you doing?

531
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:09,340
You have to obey orders!

532
00:28:09,340 --> 00:28:10,730
To hell with orders!

533
00:28:32,470 --> 00:28:33,530
Someone's coming!

534
00:28:36,640 --> 00:28:37,430
Why did you come back?

535
00:28:37,430 --> 00:28:38,360
I won't be a liability.

536
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,440
I know how to load a gun.

537
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,570
Stop with this. Run!

538
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:42,680
Take cover!

539
00:28:46,710 --> 00:28:47,400
This way!

540
00:28:54,740 --> 00:28:55,870
Keep your head down!

541
00:29:44,780 --> 00:29:45,630
Are you alright?

542
00:29:45,630 --> 00:29:46,260
Let's go!

543
00:29:48,450 --> 00:29:49,050
Up.

544
00:29:49,350 --> 00:29:49,910
Go!

545
00:29:51,180 --> 00:29:58,140
[Shanghai]

546
00:30:00,750 --> 00:30:01,620
Mrs. Meng.

547
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:02,310
Is Wanfu inside?

548
00:30:02,310 --> 00:30:02,880
Yes.

549
00:30:06,910 --> 00:30:07,630
Wanfu.

550
00:30:08,090 --> 00:30:09,420
I need to go out now.

551
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:10,980
Where are you heading?

552
00:30:12,100 --> 00:30:13,070
Do you remember Ms. Zeng,

553
00:30:13,070 --> 00:30:14,880
who I told you about before?

554
00:30:14,900 --> 00:30:15,620
Ms. Zeng...

555
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:18,460
I remember her.

556
00:30:18,460 --> 00:30:21,170
She's in charge
of the Career Women's Club.

557
00:30:21,210 --> 00:30:22,350
I read from the newspaper

558
00:30:22,350 --> 00:30:24,530
that the club is organizing
a charity sale.

559
00:30:24,210 --> 00:30:25,230
[Recruiting volunteers for a charity sale
for refugee relief]

560
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:26,030
I'd like to pay a visit to her

561
00:30:25,250 --> 00:30:26,160
[Every little bit from citizens helps]

562
00:30:26,050 --> 00:30:27,680
and see what I can help with.

563
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:31,190
T-Then what about Mr. Tian?

564
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:34,390
He just went out, didn't he?

565
00:30:36,590 --> 00:30:38,120
The concession area is chaotic recently.

566
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:39,780
You must be careful out there.

567
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:41,130
Don't worry.

568
00:30:44,900 --> 00:30:45,480
Butler Zhu.

569
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:46,240
Mrs. Meng.

570
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:49,440
Wanfu, how are the pastries
that the customer specifically

571
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:51,370
asked you to make
for Young Master Bei's banquet

572
00:30:51,370 --> 00:30:52,200
coming along?

573
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:53,260
I'm working on them. See?

574
00:30:53,260 --> 00:30:53,980
When they're done,

575
00:30:53,980 --> 00:30:55,310
I'll have Douzi deliver them.

576
00:30:55,310 --> 00:30:58,350
No. They also asked for you
in particular to tell them

577
00:30:58,350 --> 00:31:01,160
the names, origins, and such
of these pastries.

578
00:31:01,180 --> 00:31:03,510
Deliver the food yourself when it's done.

579
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:04,750
Sure.

580
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:07,500
It's Zengshou Restaurant, right?

581
00:31:07,500 --> 00:31:08,250
Yes.

582
00:31:08,750 --> 00:31:09,400
Be quick.

583
00:31:09,420 --> 00:31:10,080
No problem.

584
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:13,830
Dear listeners,

585
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:20,880
the charity sale calls upon countrymen
from all walks of life in Shanghai

586
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:24,430
to take action.

587
00:31:25,230 --> 00:31:29,220
Please donate winter clothes
to help the refugees.

588
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:33,360
For buying coupons,

589
00:31:33,430 --> 00:31:37,600
or donating items and cash,

590
00:31:38,310 --> 00:31:43,890
please dial 14633.

591
00:31:44,750 --> 00:31:50,020
Walk-ins to our charity sale office

592
00:31:50,050 --> 00:31:54,010
at No. 37 Route A.Cohen are also welcome.

593
00:31:54,340 --> 00:31:55,200
May I have your last name?

594
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,020
I need to get you registered.

595
00:31:56,020 --> 00:31:56,680
-Alright.
-Thanks.

596
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:57,400
No problem.

597
00:31:57,570 --> 00:31:59,170
Alright. Just wait a second.

598
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:01,650
Young miss, good job.

599
00:32:01,650 --> 00:32:03,920
-Got it, thanks.
-Well done, young miss.

600
00:32:03,950 --> 00:32:05,030
Alright, bye.

601
00:32:08,190 --> 00:32:16,000
[Charity Sale for Refugee Relief]

602
00:32:09,220 --> 00:32:10,910
No problem. Sure thing.

603
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,550
Thank you for such kindness.

604
00:32:12,550 --> 00:32:13,680
Thank you for such kindness.

605
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:14,400
Put this item

606
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:16,550
in the second row,
second column over there.

607
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:17,110
Be careful.

608
00:32:17,110 --> 00:32:17,590
Yes.

609
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:18,350
No problem, ma'am.

610
00:32:18,350 --> 00:32:19,310
Sure, ma'am.

611
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:22,030
Ms. Zeng!

612
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:23,460
What's your last name?

613
00:32:23,460 --> 00:32:24,680
Got it.

614
00:32:24,720 --> 00:32:26,770
-Yujiao?
-Thank you for your kindness. Thanks.

615
00:32:26,770 --> 00:32:28,000
Yes, got it.

616
00:32:46,270 --> 00:32:47,240
Thank you!

617
00:32:47,310 --> 00:32:48,840
No problem. Take care, sir.

618
00:33:04,350 --> 00:33:05,180
Run!

619
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:07,010
[Rui Pu Bao]

620
00:33:10,890 --> 00:33:11,590
Mr. Tian!

621
00:33:14,300 --> 00:33:15,100
Get in the car!

622
00:33:17,140 --> 00:33:19,400
What are you waiting for? Get in that car!

623
00:34:31,980 --> 00:34:32,980
Hello, Mrs. Meng.

624
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:36,230
Wanfu.

625
00:34:37,850 --> 00:34:38,639
You're back.

626
00:34:39,360 --> 00:34:40,500
Got any clothes to be washed?

627
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:41,630
Bring them to me now.

628
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,330
Anything wrong?

629
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:00,940
A serious incident happened.

630
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:08,730
Someone tried to

631
00:35:09,150 --> 00:35:11,750
assassinate Mr. Tian
at Zengshou Restaurant.

632
00:35:12,570 --> 00:35:14,380
But he didn't die.

633
00:35:15,630 --> 00:35:18,070
I was delivering pastries
to Zengshou Restaurant, right?

634
00:35:18,070 --> 00:35:19,670
Upon reaching the entrance,

635
00:35:19,670 --> 00:35:21,570
I heard gunshots
from inside the restaurant.

636
00:35:21,570 --> 00:35:22,710
It was so loud.

637
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:23,920
Then I saw Qi

638
00:35:23,940 --> 00:35:25,580
escorting Mr. Tian out.

639
00:35:25,710 --> 00:35:27,190
They were approaching the car

640
00:35:27,190 --> 00:35:28,500
when a gunshot rang out from somewhere

641
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:29,740
across the street.

642
00:35:29,820 --> 00:35:31,110
Good thing I acted fast enough

643
00:35:31,110 --> 00:35:32,580
to push Mr. Tian away.

644
00:35:32,670 --> 00:35:33,870
The bullet whizzed

645
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:34,880
right past me.

646
00:35:35,030 --> 00:35:36,030
Are you alright?

647
00:35:37,070 --> 00:35:39,470
Y-Yes, I am. I didn't get hurt.

648
00:35:39,630 --> 00:35:41,340
Don't forget I've been to the battlefield.

649
00:35:41,340 --> 00:35:43,000
I'm great at dodging bullets.

650
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:45,410
However, one thing

651
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:47,070
really has me puzzled.

652
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,230
Chef Meng!

653
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:50,870
Chef Meng,

654
00:35:51,130 --> 00:35:52,960
Butler Zhu is asking you to make
some blood-enriching herbal soup.

655
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:54,600
Please send it to the front house
when it's done.

656
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:55,440
No problem.

657
00:35:56,050 --> 00:35:57,110
I'll be right back.

658
00:36:07,670 --> 00:36:09,240
Then what happened?

659
00:36:09,810 --> 00:36:12,840
There was an assassination attempt
against Mr. Tian at Zengshou Restaurant.

660
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:14,000
Don't start from the beginning.

661
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,730
You already covered that part.

662
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,200
My mind is all messy right now.

663
00:36:18,230 --> 00:36:20,120
W-Where was I?

664
00:36:20,270 --> 00:36:22,440
Y-You said one thing had you puzzled.

665
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:25,160
Yes. One thing really has me puzzled.

666
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:27,060
See, we just came back.

667
00:36:27,090 --> 00:36:28,580
As the car pulled up at the main house

668
00:36:28,580 --> 00:36:30,910
and Qi was escorting Mr. Tian in,

669
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:33,420
a pool of blood appeared on the floor.

670
00:36:33,450 --> 00:36:35,550
Butler Zhu immediately ordered

671
00:36:35,580 --> 00:36:37,180
to have the floor cleaned.

672
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:39,090
But the thing is, when we left

673
00:36:39,090 --> 00:36:39,930
Zengshou Restaurant,

674
00:36:39,930 --> 00:36:41,870
Mr. Tian wasn't injured at all.

675
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,770
Nothing happened on our way back either.

676
00:36:43,770 --> 00:36:45,770
How was he hurt when he reached home?

677
00:36:45,810 --> 00:36:47,720
Did he or did he not get injured?

678
00:36:47,740 --> 00:36:48,970
I'm not sure.

679
00:36:48,990 --> 00:36:50,720
It's quite puzzling, isn't it?

680
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:55,420
Who wanted to kill Mr. Tian?

681
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:58,980
I would've forgotten it
if you hadn't asked.

682
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:02,910
Flyers were scattered
as soon as the shooter fired.

683
00:37:02,910 --> 00:37:05,370
I picked one up and brought it back
in secret.

684
00:37:06,860 --> 00:37:08,640
[Eliminate all traitors;
Victory will be ours]

685
00:37:08,310 --> 00:37:11,560
It was the Anti-Japanese
Traitor Elimination Group from Chongqing.

686
00:37:08,660 --> 00:37:10,150
[Tian Jiatai the economic traitor
deserves death]

687
00:37:13,130 --> 00:37:17,930
The Bureau of Investigation and Statics
never targets the wrong man, right?

688
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:34,660
Mr. Shao, over here.

689
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:37,290
Hechen, who did this to you?

690
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,810
Mr. Shao, you're here.

691
00:37:41,970 --> 00:37:44,450
How are you? Are you badly hurt?

692
00:37:44,550 --> 00:37:47,150
Nothing serious.
All vital organs are intact.

693
00:37:47,260 --> 00:37:49,150
Mr. Shao, did you bring enough bodyguards?

694
00:37:49,150 --> 00:37:51,250
Was anyone stalking you on your way here?

695
00:37:51,250 --> 00:37:52,470
I brought enough bodyguards.

696
00:37:52,470 --> 00:37:53,670
They are all outside.

697
00:37:54,900 --> 00:37:59,230
Mr. Shao, I really didn't do anything.

698
00:37:59,340 --> 00:38:02,570
The Shanghai Municipal Council security
is useless.

699
00:38:02,710 --> 00:38:04,160
They are good-for-nothings.

700
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:08,330
Our enemy is s-so arrogant and scary.

701
00:38:08,350 --> 00:38:09,230
Right.

702
00:38:09,250 --> 00:38:11,210
Take a look at that flier.

703
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:14,230
-Hey, read the flier.
-Oh, right, it's here.

704
00:38:14,630 --> 00:38:15,500
Read it to Mr. Shao.

705
00:38:15,500 --> 00:38:19,230
It says, "Eliminate all traitors.
Victory will be ours."

706
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:22,250
"Tian Jiatai the economic traitor
deserves death."

707
00:38:22,510 --> 00:38:24,550
It's from the Anti-Japanese
Traitor Elimination Group.

708
00:38:24,550 --> 00:38:27,960
That group says I deserve death.

709
00:38:28,630 --> 00:38:31,030
The Anti-Japanese
Traitor Elimination Group?

710
00:38:31,030 --> 00:38:32,770
Those bastards in the Bureau
of Investigation and Statistics

711
00:38:32,770 --> 00:38:35,250
are no different than terrorists!

712
00:38:35,270 --> 00:38:37,970
Why do I deserve death?

713
00:38:38,110 --> 00:38:38,820
Mr. Shao,

714
00:38:39,070 --> 00:38:42,400
you know better than anyone
about the dealings

715
00:38:42,650 --> 00:38:44,480
between my factory and Kudo.

716
00:38:44,620 --> 00:38:46,300
This is so unfair to me.

717
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:58,440
Hechen,

718
00:38:59,190 --> 00:39:02,480
I know you best. In my opinion,

719
00:39:02,500 --> 00:39:05,870
you shouldn't let them frame you
for nothing.

720
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:08,630
Now that they've put you
on their black list,

721
00:39:08,630 --> 00:39:12,630
why not set your mind
to joining the new government?

722
00:39:12,860 --> 00:39:15,160
I will provide you with protection.

723
00:39:15,180 --> 00:39:17,140
No, Mr. Shao.

724
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:18,850
I can't.

725
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:21,750
I'm scared of pain and blood,

726
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:23,400
I've always been since I was a kid.

727
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:24,320
I-I am...

728
00:39:24,340 --> 00:39:26,280
not the same kind of person as you.

729
00:39:26,630 --> 00:39:28,340
Mr. Shao, you're right.

730
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:30,230
You're not after fame or fortune.

731
00:39:30,230 --> 00:39:32,840
You work as a politician
because you hope to

732
00:39:32,860 --> 00:39:34,470
bring blessings to all people.

733
00:39:34,470 --> 00:39:36,760
Deep down, you aspire to benefit everyone.

734
00:39:36,760 --> 00:39:40,260
-But who am I?
-I'm where I am because I have no choice.

735
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:42,250
I love nothing but romantic clichés.

736
00:39:42,250 --> 00:39:44,280
I enjoy nothing but gourmet and drinks.

737
00:39:44,280 --> 00:39:45,450
Mr. Shao, p-please

738
00:39:45,630 --> 00:39:48,150
spare me from all that trouble, will you?

739
00:39:48,170 --> 00:39:49,430
Just d-do me a favor...

740
00:39:50,790 --> 00:39:52,180
Oh, it hurts again.

741
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:54,070
Is there any more anesthetic?
Give me a shot.

742
00:39:54,070 --> 00:39:55,510
Anesthetic! I need it now!

743
00:39:55,510 --> 00:39:57,400
Quick! Will it hurt when I get injected?

744
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:58,110
It will, a bit.

745
00:39:58,110 --> 00:40:00,520
It will hurt? I'm so scared!

746
00:40:00,710 --> 00:40:01,900
Mr. Shao, be careful.

747
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:03,090
I-I'm worried

748
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:04,030
that I might accidentally

749
00:40:04,030 --> 00:40:05,550
-kick you in pain.
-That's possible.

750
00:40:05,550 --> 00:40:07,020
Quick, come on. Grab my arm.

751
00:40:07,020 --> 00:40:07,800
-Come over.
-Sure.

752
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:08,610
Come to this side.

753
00:40:08,610 --> 00:40:10,060
Here, grab my arm.

754
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,940
-Bear with it, Master.
-Be gentle.

755
00:40:12,940 --> 00:40:14,290
Not so hard.

756
00:40:14,310 --> 00:40:15,150
Bear with it, Master.

757
00:40:15,150 --> 00:40:18,150
-I'll hang in there. I'll be strong.
-Hechen. Hechen!

758
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:20,120
Get a good rest.

759
00:40:20,210 --> 00:40:22,080
When you recover,

760
00:40:22,670 --> 00:40:24,880
we'll devise a proper plan.

761
00:40:25,050 --> 00:40:26,560
Y-You walk Mr. Shao out.

762
00:40:26,590 --> 00:40:27,510
Can you cope without me?

763
00:40:27,510 --> 00:40:28,650
Yes, I'll be fine on my own.

764
00:40:28,650 --> 00:40:29,280
Alright then.

765
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:30,880
I can handle this. I'll stay strong.

766
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:33,670
Take care, Mr. Shao.

767
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:35,550
Mr. Shao, I'm so sorry.

768
00:40:35,630 --> 00:40:37,160
Pardon our poor reception.

769
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:39,340
Such a serious accident was unexpected.

770
00:40:39,340 --> 00:40:39,930
I'm sorry

771
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:41,110
you were received poorly.

772
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,510
I hope you won't be angry.

773
00:40:42,590 --> 00:40:43,850
Sir, an injection now?

774
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:49,150
Forget it. The pain comes and goes.

775
00:40:49,230 --> 00:40:50,560
I'm feeling better now.

776
00:40:51,710 --> 00:40:52,370
Sir,

777
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:54,710
you should change your clothes first

778
00:40:54,890 --> 00:40:56,150
to avoid an infection.

779
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:58,550
All of you, leave.

780
00:40:59,190 --> 00:40:59,920
Yes.

781
00:41:00,230 --> 00:41:00,920
You should leave too.

782
00:41:00,920 --> 00:41:01,400
Got it.

783
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:12,550
Sir, if it really hurts badly,

784
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,880
get another shot of anesthetic.

785
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:16,760
I'm good.

786
00:41:18,230 --> 00:41:21,260
Remember what I said?
All vital parts are intact.

787
00:41:22,630 --> 00:41:24,090
This is just a flesh wound.

788
00:41:26,070 --> 00:41:27,410
These fools only know

789
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,280
to attack and kill,

790
00:41:29,670 --> 00:41:31,530
regardless of rights and wrongs.

791
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:36,230
Qi, proceed to burn the factory.

792
00:41:37,510 --> 00:41:39,880
Do not make one more blunder.

793
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:42,230
Sir, they've sent an assassin to hurt you.

794
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:43,570
What's the point of burning the factory?

795
00:41:43,570 --> 00:41:45,940
Burn it. Just do as I say.

796
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:47,570
Make the whole thing

797
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:51,480
look like the Bureau
of Investigation and Statistics' doing.

798
00:41:51,480 --> 00:41:52,440
Arrange for it now.

799
00:41:52,440 --> 00:41:53,070
Yes.

800
00:42:02,940 --> 00:42:05,230
[Wuhan, by the Yangtze River]
